President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Texas and ordered federal aid to help with the response efforts following an explosion that began on April 17, 2013. The Department of Homeland Security and FEMA will coordinate relief efforts to alleviate the suffering and hardship caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to provide necessary resources and equipment to help with the situation. Emergency protective measures and direct federal assistance will be provided at 75 percent federal funding. Kevin L. Hannes has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.